</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA08846FFC6DC6FFF6AFEEA137FFECD" blockId="18.[192,1095,257,282]" box="[192,1095,257,282]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B96B5454FFC6DC6FFF6AFEEA1650FECE" bold="true" box="[192,360,257,281]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Seasonality.</emphasis>
Adults are known only from the month of July and August.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA08846FFC6DC6FFF6AFEAA1394FE8D" blockId="18.[192,1196,321,346]" box="[192,1196,321,346]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B96B5454FFC6DC6FFF6AFEAA1661FE8E" bold="true" box="[192,345,321,345]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Bionomics.</emphasis>
The presumed habitat is seasonal mixed forest in protected canyons.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C305DBCDFFC6DC6FFF6AFE6914CCFE6D" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA08846FFC6DC6FFF6AFE6914CCFE6D" blockId="18.[192,1440,386,442]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
